York Yankees 6-4 in the opener of their three-game interleague
series at Citi Field.  Ike Davis hit a three-run homer and the Mets scored five
runs in the first inning off  Andy Pettitte .  Alex Rodriguez and Andruw Jones hit solo home runs for the
Yankees to make it 5-2 before David Wrightâ€™s run-scoring double
gave the Mets a 6-2 lead after seven innings.  The Yankees pulled within two runs on a two-run homer by
